sub_title: GP, PhD at Radboudumc, EU ITN Research Fellow, MSc in psychology
summary:
After graduating as a General Practitioner in Tunisia, I completed an MSc in Psychology of Mental health in London awarded with Distinction. 

I then realised that research in Mental Health is more than a passion for me. Therefore, I decided to complete a PhD. I got accepted to be part of the prestigious ETUDE programme funded by the European Union (Marie Sklodowska-Curie Fellowship Programme). 

I'm now completing my PhD in medical science about Functional Disorders at Radboud UMC in the Netherlands (ESR7).
